caption: Great spot! Great food at a great price! Worth the a stop and the Legos are awesome!

This is a small business owned and operated by an immigrant,  raising her son.   The food is prepared fresh every time.  It is delicious.   The menu is bountiful with choices for everyone to include surprises from other cultures.   The prices are reasonable.  I would pay 3 times as much just to support them and enjoy the love.
Everything was subpar and way too salty, and the bacon was not very good.
Amazing breakfast, incredible French toast platter....great coffee. Love the vibes🙏🏼🙏🏼🙌🏽
great brunch selections high quality thanks to Sergio!
Awesome little diner.
Always love this place. COVID UPDATE: It says no dine in available on google maps, but they are serving inside their restaurant!
Solid food and nice owners.

The food was good (not amazing, but solid). However, I’ve never waiting so long for breakfast in my life. Would not go back. There are plenty of better breakfast spots with far better service to go to.
Great food
Straightforward diner. Very nice staff. Even though I usually dine in, they are open for pickup during the lockdown and all the food was still really great.
Super cute, and cozy spot with hospitable staff and DELICIOUS food. Visited a few weeks ago when I was in town and I will be coming back on my next DC trip
This spot is wonderful,  love it
They were closed an hour after it said they opened 😞

Would give this place more than 5 stars if I could! This is a quintessential mom & pop spot, and the quality of food is amazing. Handmade bread, freshly made guacamole- not something I’ve found at any other breakfast spots in DC. My boyfriend said the chorizo burrito was the best burrito he’s ever had (and he’s had his fair share of burritos!). The place is small and family run, so it’s a refreshing change from the big chains. Highly recommend!

I had high hopes for this place but was pretty disappointed. It’s a cute little diner but basically just that. The service is honestly so bad it’s crazy we lasted for our food. There isn’t enough space for anyone besides the people at the tables and that is cutting it close. The food was pretty good but the amount of time it took to order and sit was absolutely not worth the wait. Parts of our order never came but we were still charged and received the food after we paid. Several people left before us and honestly, we should have gone with them. If you have another option, definitely chose that over this place.
Lovely little cafe for our breakfast

Amazing food and coffee. Short stay in DC ended with brunch at Flip it. This small restaurant is the best diner we’ve ever been too (NYC resident). Only down side is that it’s small and has limited seating. Skip the ihop around the corner and try Flip it.
I would give this place 6 stars if I could. Everything is excellent and the staff is very nice.

I really don’t want to give this place any starts because of their employee The spanish waitress decided she was going to seat people she knew first before us customers who were there way before. She came up to us saying “are you waiting for a table? Those men will have the booth because they were there first” mind you before she came up to us I heard her say to them “yes you’ll get the booth” She acted confused about the situation saying “huh?” She knew she was wrong because she came up to us with an explanation before anyone said anything to her. I was really excited to eat there but I’m glad I seen how their service really is before I gave them my money.
Chicken was ehhh

Can't speak on the food bc I was racially profiled and and asked to wait and let some ppl who came in after me sit down before me. So yea unless ur the typical  lighter skintoned person you'll enjoy urself. If ur a lil darker you probably want to take your  time and money else where

I come here often with my coworkers. The food is very delicious although there are a few items that I wouldn't get again. I do think they're a bit overpriced, but sometimes you feel like going out for lunch rather than going to fast food.  It's kind of strange to suggest getting french fries, but their fries are absolutely delicious.
I forget if I reviewed this place before. Either way the food is excellent. Such a gem in the city. I love the baleada. The horchata is amazing and authentic too. Can't wait to go back.
The food is sssooooo good! Nice home touch within a reasonable price. Found a new favorite place ☺

A cozy mom and pop spot with outstanding breakfast. Good service and even better food. Chorizo omelette was fantastic - probably one of the best diner omelettes I've ever had.  Will definitely be back!
Coziest little place with great food, friendly service, and  homey food for a great price.
Amazing food and service! This is a small business that is clearly popular and so they do get very busy. Be patient and I promise the food is worth it!

Too busy and completely understaffed. We waited an hour and our order had not been taken.  Got in at 12:10 on Sunday. Seated 12:20. Drink order taken at 1pm. We got our coffee at 1:05. But no one had taken our order.  They have one person in the front taking orders, bussing, and serving. It's not fair to the worker or customers to be so short staffed.
This is a terrific little place. The food was delicious & the service was great.

I ordered the banana foster French toast and my friend ordered the divorced eggs. Mine wasn't good. Hers was. Reviews had already warned not to order American food though. I second that. Otherwise cool environment and great customer service.
Service was great!!!  But the attempt to make Eggs Benedict was poor 😢😢
Lovely little diner
This is one of my favorite places to get a delicious breakfast. A hidden gem of a place: family run, excellent service, and delicious food. I highly recommend their Oaxaca Omelet!
Great food great ambience. Church next door if you feel lost in this world.

Delicious breakfast foods, fast service, and fair prices make it hard to stay away.  Really love their banana pancakes, corn beef hash, and horchata, but can honestly say everything I’ve tried has tasted great.  Overall highly recommend this low key DC diner to anyone in looking for a good bite.
Great food and delightful staff--and pretty cheap prices!
Small family run place. If you get a table, you will not be disappointed.
The best quinoa soup in the city!
This place has a really amazing breakfast food. The menu has tons of great different options. Casual neighborhood cafe with friendliest staff!

Probably the best place I've ever ate at in DC!! Hands down! The service was exceptionally well. The food is beyond delicious. I ordered the biscuits and gravy and a side of salmon cakes and I was beyond pleased with that taste of the food. Next time I'm in DC, I'm for sure coming here first thing. Do yourself a favor and come eat here. You won't be disappointed.
Great food, great service!
(Translated by Google) Delicious divorced eggs!  (Original) Delicious huevos divorciados!
It's what you're looking for
Great food, amazing service, and cool atmosphere. Worth it!
Fast friendly service with very good food.
Great casual, low key spot for lunch.  The chorizo burrito was the bomb.

Great food, responsive friendly servers, and cozy atmosphere... That is if you manage to snag a table. Only about 5-6 four-tops and four seats at the counter. Everyone loves this place, so it makes sense. You just have to get in at a good time, it is well worth it!
The food was phenomenal. Good prices. Definitely worth the stop.
Amazing. It's a little small, but the staff is friendly and the food is delicious.
Now THIS is a diner!
(Translated by Google) thanks  (Original) Dank
I came by on a Weds and they were closed. Now here on Thursday, enjoying a coffee and breakfast sandwich. Loving it!

This place is outstanding! Excellent breakfast classics, fresh baked bread, huge portions, great value, and super friendly. It's pretty small (only 5 tables and 4 bar seats) so you may expect a wait during busy times. Staff is small so service can also be a bit harried when full, though they're very accommodating. Try the omlets (esp the Greek quinoa) or the avacado toast w/poached eggs. Worth the wait.
Really friendly service and great food.  The Reuben and the coffee are always on point.
Good value for money. Very relaxed atmosphere and complaisant staff.
Not as popular as it should be considering, location, quality, and price. Go here before they're discovered.
Food was great. Limited seating room so expect a short wait, although staff is very accommodating (can order coffee while you wait).
If you want a freshly cooked breakfast this is a great place. Great service as well.
One of my favorite places to go in Columbia Heights. Great food at reasonable price. Be prepared to wait a short while as there are not many tables.
Great Customer Service & Great Food
Good food. The menu is quite varied, great tacos but also great waffles. I also like the owners, really try to ensure you have a good experience. It is a smaller place than the one they had in NE
Delicious food and welcoming staff.

Love this place. Everything I've had so far has been delicious, but I would say that their waffles/french toast game is particularly amazing. Only drawback is that there isn't a lot of seating, so be prepared to wait during peak times.
Great service, wonderful menu
Banana French toast was awesome. Loved everything we got; service was great.  Great vibes.  Best breakfast/brunch spot in DC.
Great food, great service, one of my favorites
The food was great, the hospitality wasn't good. Could've asked me how was my food and if there was anything i needed.

Cute and cozy diner with delicious food that feels like someone’s made it for you at home. It’s not fancy or plated with any kind of pretentiousness which is the charm of it. I’ve been coming for breakfast food here for over a year and am always happy with the service and food!
Great food and some newly added menu items!  Nice and quiet early on Saturday.
The food is tasty. Whenever I want something to eat, I can always rely on good flavor. The staff is friendly.

Amazing family-owned hole-in-the-wall diner in the heart of Columbia Heights. I ordered the eggs benedict - portions were large, and the wait staff was super friendly and kept the coffee flowing. Will definitely be back when I'm in the area!
Love the quinoa soup
Ordered the early-bird breakfast burrito today and it was amazing!!! The place is quiet and warm and the food is made from scratch, homemade and hits the spot. Good service and it’s family owned!
Really great food!
Everything was delicious!  Apparently, a fairly new establishment. Very small, so get there early on the weekends
Columbia Heights best kept secret. Menu is amazing. Have been here numerous times, and always satisfied. Wait staff is incredibly nice, definitely recommend
Really liked this place, small and cozy with cute decor and great food. The diner I've been looking for in DC!
Great food! Great service! Very friendly and attentive family that runs the shop. Definitely going back to try more good food.
Very good! Pleasantly surprised! SpansiS owned authentic food and gresg prices. It's tight spot so show up early if wanna grab a seat. Thanks for great service. Definetly coming again.

Best lunch. Well, I ordered the Lomo dinner... and it was DELICIOUS. I've eaten it a million times oit of to go containers, so this was almost fancy, on a real dish. But the skirt steak was perfectly cooked. I would have loved more onions but tjats just me. The fries were crispy and the sauce had GREAT flavor. We also ordered the chicken nachos.. that was a massive plate. And no one complained! All in all a phenomonal meal! Can't wait to come back to D.C. We will be back here!
Great food quick, large selection

Wow! This might just be my new favourite place in DC! What an amazing little place, just a few tables and a very homey vibe. I had their Oaxaca Omelete, which took my taste buds on a journey through the mountains of southern Mexico. 11/10 recommend!  Hidden gem that's really cheap for what you get! Also great music choice! My only recommendation for the owners, will be better lighting. I'll be back very soon :-)

Tiny place but the food is good. Only 25 seats at 5 tables & a 3-seat counter. I only had breakfast, but it was good & at a reasonable price. They serve breakfast all day, but for some reason don't start serving until 9 am
(Translated by Google) The place is quite good the food I like a lot and the attention is excellent  (Original) El lugar es bastante bueno la comida me gusta mucho y la atencion excelente
Solid diner food at great prices with amazing service! They’ll definitely make you feel at home.
Excellent food and service.

This is your awesome 'hole in the wall'.  Its a small diner, set just off the main cross-road.  We came for breakfast... service was awesome, very friendly and food was timely and delicious.  Would definitely eat here again if in the neighborhood.
New favorite breakfast spot. The portions are huge. The prices are super reasonable. And, the staff are the sweetest. They'll also modify anything you'd like to your liking. I'll be back, very soon!
Nice diner with fun takes ok traditional favorites. Chorizo and eggs were amazing.
Great local diner. Food is always good. Owners are always friendly. Happy to have this place nearby.
Delicious breakfast!  Open at 7 on weekdays.  Piping hot coffee, a wide selection of favorites, and friendly service.  A really great neighborhood spot.
Welcoming atmosphere, service was friendly and not overbearing.  Many tempting items on the menu, and good coffee.  Breads baked on premises.  Breakfast served all day.

my only regret is that I didn't stop in sooner. other reviews are right, you can tell there's a lot of love in this food. Also, the horchata is real, not a mix, and they bake their own bread. seriously, this place is great! I'll be back for breakfast this weekend.
Great meal, atmosphere and service.  Highly recommended.
Great service. Good food.
Really tasty and affordable. I hope they keep the tipsy banana pancakes on the menu!
Did not have a chance to enjoy the food, but it was clean, quiet and the host has nice manners.
Best place in the neighborhood.

This wonderful diner, which all my friends and I call “Luke’s,” offers endless coffee, sweet family banter, and a menu that updates with the seasons! I bring all my favorite humans here and we debate the finer qualities of why the beloved Luke’s is a true gem.  Come for the salmon cake, stay for the homey feeling. Prices are right on point, and the food is top notch.

Been here three times and had great experiences each time. It's a cozy space with very friendly service and the food is delicious, affordable, and filling. Food comes out quickly and steaming hot, just as it should at a diner. So glad to have this place in the neighborhood!
Awesome service - they really go the extra mile to make you feel at home here. Delicious and affordable food with plenty of options for breakfast and lunch. Very clean yet cozy atmosphere.
Food is so damn good! Very small & clean inside. Get there early on weekends
Great family owned diner, the food and service was excellent!
Great, cheap breakfast and Mexican food!
